text.__SUMMARY__: Carex azuayae is a species of flowering plant in the sedge family, Cyperaceae. It is endemic to Ecuador. Its natural habitat is subtropical or tropical high-altitude grassland.
text.References: N. Pitman (2004). "Carex azuayae". The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species. IUCN. 2004: e.T45147A10983435. doi:10.2305/IUCN.UK.2004.RLTS.T45147A10983435.en. Retrieved 6 January 2018.
